\n* ''[[Troopers Three]]'' (1930) as 'Sunny'\n* ''[[The King of Jazz]]'' (1930) as Automobile Owner ('Springtime') / Rear End of Horse / Charles\n* ''[[All Quiet on the Western Front (1930 film)|All Quiet on the Western Front]]'' (1930) as Tjaden\n* ''[[The Little Accident]]'' (1930) as Hicks\n* ''Under Montana Skies'' (1930) as Sunshine\n* ''[[The Spoilers (1930 film)|The Spoilers]]'' (1930) as Slapjack Simms\n* ''[[Her Man (1930 film)|Her Man]]'' (1930) as The Swede\n* ''[[See America Thirst]]'' (1930) as Slim\n* ''[[Free Love (film)|Free Love]]'' (1930) as Gas Inspector\n* ''[[Many a Slip (film)|Many a Slip]]'' (1931) as Hopkins\n* ''[[The Front Page (1931 film)|The Front Page]]'' (1931) as Irving Pincus\n* ''El Tenorio del harem'' (1931) as El corneta\n* ''[[Bad Sister (1931 film)|Bad Sister]]'' (1931) as Sam\n* ''[[Lasca of the Rio Grande]]'' (1931) as 'Crabapple' Thompson\n* ''[[Reckless Living]]'' (1931) as The Drunk\n* ''[[Heaven on Earth (1931 film)|Heaven on Earth]]'' (1931) as The Jeweler \n* ''[[The Unexpected Father]]'' (1932) as Jasper Jones\n* ''[[Racing Youth]]'' (1932) as Slim\n* ''[[Tom Brown of Culver]]'' (1932) as Elmer (Slim) Whitman\n* ''[[Air Mail (film)|Air Mail]]'' (1932) as 'Slim' McCune\n* ''[[They Just Had to Get Married]]'' (1932) as Sam Sutton\n* ''[[Out All Night (1933 film)|Out All Night]]'' (1933) as Ronald Colgate\n* ''[[Horse Play]]'' (1933) as Slim Perkins\n* ''[[Her First Mate]]'' (1933) as John Homer\n* ''[[Love, Honor, and Oh Baby!]]'' (1933) as Mark Reed\n* ''[[Love Birds (1934 film)|Love Birds]]'' (1934) as Henry Whipple\n* ''[[Their Big Moment]]'' (1934) as Bill Ambrose\n* ''[[Life Begins at 40 (film)|Life Begins at 40]]'' (1935) as T. Watterson Meriwether\n* ''[[The Farmer Takes a Wife (film)|The Farmer Takes a Wife]]'' (1935) as Fortune Friendly\n* ''[[Way Down East (1935 film)|Way Down East]]'' (1935) as Constable Seth Holcomb\n* ''[[The Country Doctor (1936 film)|The Country Doctor]]'' (1936) as Constable Jim Ogden\n* ''